title: Introduction to React and JSX
description: Learn the core concepts of React, its purpose, and how it works. Master JSX (JavaScript XML), the syntax extension that lets you write HTML-like structures in your JavaScript, and create a simple, functional React component.

title: Components, Props, and State
description: Dive deeper into components, the fundamental building blocks of any React application. Understand props (properties) for passing data down between components, and learn to manage internal component data and create interactive user interfaces using the useState Hook.

title: Handling Events and Conditional Rendering
description: Learn how to capture and respond to user input (like clicks and form changes) by implementing event handlers. Also, explore techniques for conditional rendering to display different content or components based on the current application state or specific conditions.
